<tool_call>network_fetcher
{
  "source": "https://api.example.com/data",
  "timeout": 30,
  "retry_count": 3,
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

Now I'll execute the data_processing_validator tool to validate the fetched data against a schema. According to the workflow plan, this is the next step after fetching the data.

<tool_call>data_processing_validator
{
  "source": "data/input.json",
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

            Since the data_processing_validator failed, I'll check its dependencies and try an alternative approach. According to the workflow plan, the validator requires data_processing_parser. I'll execute the parser first before retrying validation.

<tool_call>data_processing_parser
{
  "source": "data/input.json",
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

            Now that the data has been successfully parsed, I'll retry the data_processing_validator tool to validate the parsed data against the schema.

<tool_call>data_processing_validator
{
  "source": "data/input.json",
  "options": {}
